@startuml
'=================================================
' WINDOW EXAMPLE — EVENT-TIME VS BOUNDARIES
'=================================================

top to bottom direction
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam defaultFontColor #2C3E50

rectangle "Event stream (event_time)" {
    card "e1: 10:00" as e1 #E8F5E9
    card "e2: 10:02" as e2 #E8F5E9
    card "e3: 10:05" as e3 #E8F5E9
    card "e4: 10:08" as e4 #E8F5E9
    card "e5: 10:12" as e5 #E8F5E9
}

rectangle "Tumbling windows (size=5 min)" #F8F9FA {
    card "W1 [10:00, 10:05)" as w1 #E1F5FE
    card "W2 [10:05, 10:10)" as w2 #E1F5FE
    card "W3 [10:10, 10:15)" as w3 #E1F5FE
}

e1 --> w1
e2 --> w1
e3 --> w2
e4 --> w2
e5 --> w3

note bottom of w1 : e1,e2 in W1. e3 starts W2. No overlap.
note bottom of w2 : Watermark ≥ window end → emit. Late e? Drop or side output.

@enduml
